{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 05 — Difference-in-Differences Quasi-Experiment\n",
    "\n",
    "**Project:** Chicago Transit & Logistics Intelligence Platform  \n",
    "**Author:** Hari Etta  \n",
    "**Purpose:** Measure the causal effect of the Route 36 frequency increase using DiD.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why DiD, not an A/B test\n",
    "CTA cannot randomly assign commuters to routes. The data is observational.\n",
    "A naive before/after comparison of Route 36 would confound the treatment\n",
    "effect with seasonal trends, weather, and citywide ridership patterns.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Difference-in-differences** removes these confounders by using Route 49\n",
    "(Western) as a control — a route with similar ridership and corridor type\n",
    "that did NOT receive a frequency change in the study period.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Causal model\n",
    "```\n",
    "DiD estimate = (Route36_post − Route36_pre) − (Route49_post − Route49_pre)\n",
    "rides ~ β₀ + β₁·treatment + β₂·post + β₃·(treatment × post) + ε\n",
    "```\n",
    "β₃ is the causal estimate: additional riders/day caused by the frequency increase.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Notebook structure\n",
    "1. Load ridership for Routes 36 and 49\n",
    "2. Define intervention date and pre/post periods\n",
    "3. Parallel trends validation — visual + Granger pre-test\n",
    "4. OLS DiD regression via statsmodels\n",
    "5. Results: β₃ coefficient, 95% CI, p-value\n",
    "6. Four-quadrant DiD visualisation\n",
    "7. Placebo test — same regression on pre-intervention period\n",
    "8. Interpretation and policy implication"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os, sys, warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, '..')\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.dates as mdates\n",
    "import matplotlib.patches as mpatches\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import statsmodels.formula.api as smf\n",
    "from scipy import stats\n",
    "from datetime import date\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid')\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (14, 6)\n",
    "plt.rcParams['font.size'] = 11\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Experiment parameters ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "TREATMENT_ROUTE   = '36'     # Broadway — received frequency increase\n",
    "CONTROL_ROUTE     = '49'     # Western  — no change\n",
    "INTERVENTION_DATE = pd.Timestamp('2023-07-10')  # documented CTA change\n",
    "STUDY_START       = pd.Timestamp('2023-05-01')\n",
    "STUDY_END         = pd.Timestamp('2023-10-31')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('DiD experiment parameters:')\n",
    "print(f'  Treatment route   : {TREATMENT_ROUTE} (Broadway)')\n",
    "print(f'  Control route     : {CONTROL_ROUTE} (Western)')\n",
    "print(f'  Intervention date : {INTERVENTION_DATE.date()}')\n",
    "print(f'  Study window      : {STUDY_START.date()} → {STUDY_END.date()}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load and Prepare Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "try:\n",
    "    df_all = pd.read_parquet('../data/processed/features.parquet')\n",
    "except FileNotFoundError:\n",
    "    df_all = pd.read_csv('../data/sample/cta_ridership_sample.csv', parse_dates=['service_date'])\n",
    "    df_all['rides'] = pd.to_numeric(df_all['rides'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "\n",
    "df_all['service_date'] = pd.to_datetime(df_all['service_date'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filter to study routes and window\n",
    "df = df_all[\n",
    "    df_all['route'].isin([TREATMENT_ROUTE, CONTROL_ROUTE])\n",
    "    & (df_all['service_date'] >= STUDY_START)\n",
    "    & (df_all['service_date'] <= STUDY_END)\n",
    "].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# DiD indicator variables\n",
    "df['treatment'] = (df['route'] == TREATMENT_ROUTE).astype(int)\n",
    "df['post']      = (df['service_date'] >= INTERVENTION_DATE).astype(int)\n",
    "df['treat_x_post'] = df['treatment'] * df['post']  # the DiD interaction term\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Study dataset: {len(df)} rows')\n",
    "print(f\"\\nRoute {TREATMENT_ROUTE}: {len(df[df['route']==TREATMENT_ROUTE])} rows\")\n",
    "print(f\"Route {CONTROL_ROUTE}: {len(df[df['route']==CONTROL_ROUTE])} rows\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Descriptive summary\n",
    "summary = df.groupby(['route','post'])['rides'].agg(['mean','std','count']).round(1)\n",
    "summary.index = summary.index.set_levels(\n",
    "    [summary.index.levels[0],\n",
    "     ['Pre-intervention','Post-intervention']]\n",
    ")\n",
    "print('\\nRidership summary by group and period:')\n",
    "print(summary)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Raw Pre/Post Comparison (naive — confounded)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Naive before-after (wrong — does not remove confounders)\n",
    "t36_pre  = df[(df['route'] == TREATMENT_ROUTE) & (df['post'] == 0)]['rides'].mean()\n",
    "t36_post = df[(df['route'] == TREATMENT_ROUTE) & (df['post'] == 1)]['rides'].mean()\n",
    "naive_effect = t36_post - t36_pre\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Route 36 pre-intervention avg  : {t36_pre:.0f} riders/day')\n",
    "print(f'Route 36 post-intervention avg : {t36_post:.0f} riders/day')\n",
    "print(f'Naive before-after effect      : +{naive_effect:.0f} riders/day')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('WARNING: This naive estimate is CONFOUNDED by seasonal trends.')\n",
    "print('DiD removes confounders using Route 49 as the counterfactual.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Parallel Trends Validation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Pre-intervention data only\n",
    "pre_df = df[df['post'] == 0].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Weekly averages\n",
    "pre_weekly = (\n",
    "    pre_df.set_index('service_date')\n",
    "    .groupby('route')['rides']\n",
    "    .resample('W').mean()\n",
    "    .reset_index()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(18, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Weekly ridership — pre period\n",
    "for route, color, label in [\n",
    "    (TREATMENT_ROUTE, 'steelblue', f'Route {TREATMENT_ROUTE} (Broadway — Treatment)'),\n",
    "    (CONTROL_ROUTE,   'coral',     f'Route {CONTROL_ROUTE} (Western — Control)')\n",
    "]:\n",
    "    sub = pre_weekly[pre_weekly['route'] == route]\n",
    "    axes[0].plot(sub['service_date'], sub['rides'], color=color, linewidth=2.5,\n",
    "                 marker='o', markersize=4, label=label)\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Parallel Trends — Pre-Intervention Period\\n(Both routes must trend similarly for DiD to be valid)',\n",
    "                  fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Weekly Avg Daily Rides')\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('Date')\n",
    "axes[0].legend()\n",
    "axes[0].xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%b %d'))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Difference in weekly ridership (pre-period only)\n",
    "r36_weekly = pre_weekly[pre_weekly['route'] == TREATMENT_ROUTE].set_index('service_date')['rides']\n",
    "r49_weekly = pre_weekly[pre_weekly['route'] == CONTROL_ROUTE].set_index('service_date')['rides']\n",
    "diff = (r36_weekly - r49_weekly).dropna()\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[1].plot(diff.index, diff.values, color='purple', linewidth=2, marker='o', markersize=4)\n",
    "axes[1].axhline(diff.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=1.5,\n",
    "                label=f'Mean diff = {diff.mean():.0f}')\n",
    "axes[1].fill_between(diff.index,\n",
    "                     diff.mean() - diff.std(),\n",
    "                     diff.mean() + diff.std(),\n",
    "                     alpha=0.15, color='purple', label='±1 std')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Weekly Ridership Difference (Route 36 − Route 49)\\nFlat = parallel trends assumption holds',\n",
    "                  fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Difference in avg daily rides')\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('Date')\n",
    "axes[1].legend()\n",
    "axes[1].xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%b %d'))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../docs/did_parallel_trends.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Pre-period difference mean   : {diff.mean():.1f} riders/week')\n",
    "print(f'Pre-period difference std    : {diff.std():.1f} riders/week')\n",
    "print(f'Coefficient of variation     : {diff.std()/abs(diff.mean()):.3f}')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('Parallel trends assessment:')\n",
    "if diff.std() / abs(diff.mean()) < 0.3:\n",
    "    print('  PASS — Difference is stable (CV < 0.30). DiD assumption holds.')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print('  CAUTION — Some variation in pre-period difference. Review carefully.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Granger causality pre-test (does Route 36 Granger-cause Route 49 or vice versa?)\n",
    "# If yes, routes are not independent — DiD assumption is weakened\n",
    "from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import grangercausalitytests\n",
    "\n",
    "r36_daily = pre_df[pre_df['route'] == TREATMENT_ROUTE].set_index('service_date')['rides'].sort_index()\n",
    "r49_daily = pre_df[pre_df['route'] == CONTROL_ROUTE].set_index('service_date')['rides'].sort_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "combined = pd.concat([r36_daily, r49_daily], axis=1).dropna()\n",
    "combined.columns = ['r36','r49']\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Granger causality test: Does Route 36 Granger-cause Route 49? (maxlag=4)')\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    gc_results = grangercausalitytests(combined[['r49','r36']], maxlag=4, verbose=False)\n",
    "    for lag, result in gc_results.items():\n",
    "        f_stat = result[0]['ssr_ftest'][0]\n",
    "        p_val  = result[0]['ssr_ftest'][1]\n",
    "        print(f'  Lag {lag}: F={f_stat:.3f}, p={p_val:.3f} {\"✓ not significant\" if p_val > 0.05 else \"✗ SIGNIFICANT\"}')\n",
    "    print()\n",
    "    print('Interpretation: p > 0.05 at all lags confirms routes are independent.')\n",
    "    print('DiD parallel trends assumption is supported.')\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f'Granger test skipped (insufficient data): {e}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. DiD OLS Regression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# OLS: rides ~ treatment + post + treatment:post\n",
    "# The coefficient on treatment:post IS the DiD causal estimate\n",
    "\n",
    "model = smf.ols(\n",
    "    formula='rides ~ treatment + post + treat_x_post',\n",
    "    data=df\n",
    ").fit(cov_type='HC3')  # heteroskedasticity-robust standard errors\n",
    "\n",
    "print(model.summary())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Extract the key result\n",
    "did_estimate = model.params['treat_x_post']\n",
    "did_se       = model.bse['treat_x_post']\n",
    "did_pval     = model.pvalues['treat_x_post']\n",
    "did_ci_low   = model.conf_int().loc['treat_x_post', 0]\n",
    "did_ci_high  = model.conf_int().loc['treat_x_post', 1]\n",
    "naive_bias   = naive_effect - did_estimate\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "print('  DIFFERENCE-IN-DIFFERENCES RESULT')\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "print(f'  DiD estimate (β₃)   : +{did_estimate:.0f} riders/day')\n",
    "print(f'  Standard error       : {did_se:.1f}')\n",
    "print(f'  95% CI               : [{did_ci_low:.0f}, {did_ci_high:.0f}]')\n",
    "print(f'  p-value              : {did_pval:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'  Significant at 1%?   : {\"YES\" if did_pval < 0.01 else \"NO\"}')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(f'  Naive before-after   : +{naive_effect:.0f} riders/day')\n",
    "print(f'  Confounder bias removed: {naive_bias:.0f} riders/day')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('  INTERPRETATION:')\n",
    "print(f'  The Route 36 frequency increase CAUSED an additional')\n",
    "print(f'  {did_estimate:.0f} daily riders (95% CI: {did_ci_low:.0f}–{did_ci_high:.0f}).')\n",
    "print(f'  Without DiD, the naive estimate would have OVERSTATED')\n",
    "print(f'  the effect by {abs(naive_bias):.0f} riders ({abs(naive_bias/naive_effect)*100:.0f}%).')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Four-Quadrant DiD Visualisation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Group means for the four quadrants\n",
    "means = df.groupby(['route','post'])['rides'].mean().unstack()\n",
    "means.columns = ['Pre','Post']\n",
    "\n",
    "r36_pre  = means.loc[TREATMENT_ROUTE, 'Pre']\n",
    "r36_post = means.loc[TREATMENT_ROUTE, 'Post']\n",
    "r49_pre  = means.loc[CONTROL_ROUTE,   'Pre']\n",
    "r49_post = means.loc[CONTROL_ROUTE,   'Post']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Counterfactual: what Route 36 would have looked like without intervention\n",
    "r36_counterfactual = r36_pre + (r49_post - r49_pre)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(18, 7))\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Left: four-quadrant means ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "x = [0, 1]\n",
    "axes[0].plot(x, [r36_pre, r36_post], 'b-o', linewidth=3, markersize=10,\n",
    "             label=f'Route {TREATMENT_ROUTE} (Broadway — Treatment)', zorder=5)\n",
    "axes[0].plot(x, [r49_pre, r49_post], 'r-o', linewidth=3, markersize=10,\n",
    "             label=f'Route {CONTROL_ROUTE} (Western — Control)', zorder=5)\n",
    "axes[0].plot(x, [r36_pre, r36_counterfactual], 'b--', linewidth=2, alpha=0.5,\n",
    "             label=f'Route {TREATMENT_ROUTE} counterfactual (no treatment)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# DiD arrow\n",
    "axes[0].annotate('', xy=(1, r36_post), xytext=(1, r36_counterfactual),\n",
    "                 arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='<->', color='green', lw=2.5))\n",
    "axes[0].text(1.03, (r36_post + r36_counterfactual) / 2,\n",
    "             f'DiD = +{did_estimate:.0f}\\n(95% CI: {did_ci_low:.0f}–{did_ci_high:.0f})',\n",
    "             color='green', fontsize=11, va='center', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].set_xticks([0, 1])\n",
    "axes[0].set_xticklabels(['Pre-intervention\\n(May–Jul 9, 2023)',\n",
    "                          'Post-intervention\\n(Jul 10–Oct 31, 2023)'], fontsize=10)\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('DiD Four-Quadrant Chart\\nAverage Daily Ridership by Group × Period',\n",
    "                  fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Average Daily Rides')\n",
    "axes[0].legend(loc='upper left', fontsize=9)\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlim(-0.15, 1.35)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add value labels\n",
    "for val, xpos, ypos in [\n",
    "    (r36_pre, 0, r36_pre), (r36_post, 1, r36_post),\n",
    "    (r49_pre, 0, r49_pre), (r49_post, 1, r49_post)\n",
    "]:\n",
    "    axes[0].annotate(f'{val:.0f}', xy=(xpos, ypos),\n",
    "                     xytext=(-18, 6), textcoords='offset points', fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Right: full time series ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "weekly = (\n",
    "    df.set_index('service_date')\n",
    "    .groupby('route')['rides']\n",
    "    .resample('W').mean()\n",
    "    .reset_index()\n",
    ")\n",
    "for route, color, label in [\n",
    "    (TREATMENT_ROUTE, 'steelblue', f'Route {TREATMENT_ROUTE} (Treatment)'),\n",
    "    (CONTROL_ROUTE,   'coral',     f'Route {CONTROL_ROUTE} (Control)')\n",
    "]:\n",
    "    sub = weekly[weekly['route'] == route]\n",
    "    axes[1].plot(sub['service_date'], sub['rides'], color=color, linewidth=2.5,\n",
    "                 label=label)\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[1].axvline(INTERVENTION_DATE, color='green', linestyle='--', linewidth=2,\n",
    "                label=f'Intervention: {INTERVENTION_DATE.date()}')\n",
    "axes[1].fill_betweenx(\n",
    "    [axes[1].get_ylim()[0] if axes[1].get_ylim()[0] else 0, 20000],\n",
    "    INTERVENTION_DATE, STUDY_END,\n",
    "    alpha=0.05, color='green'\n",
    ")\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Weekly Ridership: Treatment vs Control\\nFull Study Window', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Weekly Avg Daily Rides')\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('Date')\n",
    "axes[1].legend()\n",
    "axes[1].xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%b %Y'))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../docs/did_results.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Placebo Test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Placebo: run DiD on pre-intervention data only, with a fake intervention date\n",
    "# The estimate should be near zero if the methodology is sound\n",
    "PLACEBO_DATE = pd.Timestamp('2023-06-01')  # fake intervention — no real change\n",
    "\n",
    "placebo_df = df_all[\n",
    "    df_all['route'].isin([TREATMENT_ROUTE, CONTROL_ROUTE])\n",
    "    & (df_all['service_date'] >= STUDY_START)\n",
    "    & (df_all['service_date'] < INTERVENTION_DATE)  # pre-period only\n",
    "].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "placebo_df['treatment']    = (placebo_df['route'] == TREATMENT_ROUTE).astype(int)\n",
    "placebo_df['post']         = (placebo_df['service_date'] >= PLACEBO_DATE).astype(int)\n",
    "placebo_df['treat_x_post'] = placebo_df['treatment'] * placebo_df['post']\n",
    "\n",
    "placebo_model = smf.ols(\n",
    "    formula='rides ~ treatment + post + treat_x_post',\n",
    "    data=placebo_df\n",
    ").fit(cov_type='HC3')\n",
    "\n",
    "placebo_est    = placebo_model.params['treat_x_post']\n",
    "placebo_ci_low = placebo_model.conf_int().loc['treat_x_post', 0]\n",
    "placebo_ci_hi  = placebo_model.conf_int().loc['treat_x_post', 1]\n",
    "placebo_pval   = placebo_model.pvalues['treat_x_post']\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "print('  PLACEBO TEST RESULT')\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "print(f'  Fake intervention date : {PLACEBO_DATE.date()}')\n",
    "print(f'  Placebo DiD estimate   : {placebo_est:+.0f} riders/day')\n",
    "print(f'  95% CI                 : [{placebo_ci_low:.0f}, {placebo_ci_hi:.0f}]')\n",
    "print(f'  p-value                : {placebo_pval:.3f}')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "if placebo_pval > 0.05:\n",
    "    print('  PASS — Placebo estimate is statistically indistinguishable')\n",
    "    print('  from zero (p > 0.05). The methodology is NOT finding')\n",
    "    print('  spurious effects. The true DiD result is credible.')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print('  FAIL — Placebo estimate is significant (p < 0.05).')\n",
    "    print('  This suggests the parallel trends assumption may be violated.')\n",
    "    print('  Review control route selection before using the main result.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compare true vs placebo estimates visually\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "estimates = [did_estimate, placebo_est]\n",
    "ci_lows   = [did_ci_low,   placebo_ci_low]\n",
    "ci_highs  = [did_ci_high,  placebo_ci_hi]\n",
    "labels    = ['True DiD estimate\\n(Route 36 freq increase)', 'Placebo estimate\\n(fake intervention)']\n",
    "colors    = ['steelblue', 'coral']\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, (est, low, high, label, color) in enumerate(zip(estimates, ci_lows, ci_highs, labels, colors)):\n",
    "    ax.barh(i, est, color=color, alpha=0.7, height=0.4)\n",
    "    ax.errorbar(est, i, xerr=[[est-low],[high-est]],\n",
    "                fmt='none', color='black', capsize=6, linewidth=2)\n",
    "    ax.text(est + 5, i, f'{est:+.0f} riders/day\\n(p={did_pval:.4f if i==0 else placebo_pval:.3f})',\n",
    "            va='center', fontsize=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.axvline(0, color='black', linewidth=1.5)\n",
    "ax.set_yticks([0, 1])\n",
    "ax.set_yticklabels(labels, fontsize=11)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Estimated effect (riders/day)')\n",
    "ax.set_title('True DiD Estimate vs Placebo Test\\nPlacebo near zero confirms methodology is valid',\n",
    "             fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../docs/did_placebo.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
